message: “It’s about ending the cycle of human trafficking,” says WSP Chief John R. Batiste. “This operation not only helps protect the victims of human trafficking but also safeguards our communities from criminal activity.”

data.description: PIERCE COUNTY, Wash. — An undercover operation in Washington State to battle sex trafficking made nearly a dozen arrests and discovered in a mere four hours seven women who were victims of prostitution and three who were victims of human trafficking. The Washington State Patrol and Lakewood police...
data.title: Undercover sex trafficking operation makes nearly dozen arrests | East Idaho News
